A 36-year-old man is expected in court on Thursday after he was arrested by Port Elizabeth police on Wednesday night for dealing in mandrax in Govan Mbeki locality in Kwadwesi."This follows after the Motherwell Operational Command Centre received information of the drugs at a house in the area," police said."On searching the premises, at about 23:00, a shotgun round and more than 1 300 tablets of mandrax were found with an estimated street market value of R65 000."Police said that the suspect has been charged for dealing in mandrax as well as the illegal possession of ammunition."He will appear before the New Brighton Magistrates Court," police said.